title: SFH welcomes Mainland epidemiological experts to visit Hong Kong
content_text: To tackle the worsening situation of the fifth wave of the epidemic in Hong Kong, the Chief Executive, Mrs Carrie Lam, announced earlier that Professor Chan should be responsible for the task force of epidemiologists, co-ordinating the Department of Health (DH), the Hospital Authority (HA) and local experts to liaise with Mainland experts to assist Hong Kong in conducting epidemiological investigations and analyses. Professor Chan said, "The Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Government is grateful to the Central Authorities for providing their strongest support for the HKSAR, and have arranged for the Mainland experts to arrive in Hong Kong in such

the HKSAR, and have arranged for the Mainland experts to arrive in Hong Kong in such a short period of time to share with us their experience in anti-epidemic work and provide advice. The HKSAR Government will, in accordance with the important instructions of President Xi Jinping, assume the main responsibility to stabilise the epidemic situation early as the overriding mission at present, and mobilise all available manpower and resources and adopt all necessary measures to safeguard the lives and health of Hong Kong people and the stability of society." During the visit, the Mainland experts will meet with Professor Chan; the Director of Health, Dr Ronald

the visit, the Mainland experts will meet with Professor Chan; the Director of Health, Dr Ronald Lam; and the Chief Executive of the HA, Dr Tony Ko. They will also visit the Centre for Health Protection of the DH and its Contact Tracing Offices, etc, to learn about Hong Kong's work in epidemiological investigations, contact tracing, environmental investigations, the "StayHomeSafe" Scheme and sewage surveillance.
